Date/time at which a payment can be made, for example, if payment date is a non-business day or to indicate the first payment date of an offer.
Date/time at which the lot was purchased.
Date by which the depository stops monitoring activities of the event, for instance, accounting and tracking activities for due bills end.
Date/time at which the bondholders' or shareholders' meeting will take place.
Date/time at which the company's general meeting is scheduled, 2nd session if applicable (for example, Italy).
Date/time at which the company's general meeting is scheduled, 3rd session if applicable (for example, Italy).
Issuer or issuer's agent deadline to respond, with an election instruction, to an outstanding offer or privilege.
Last day an investor can become a lead plaintiff.
Last date/time a holder can request to defer delivery of securities pursuant to a notice of guaranteed delivery or other required documentation.
Date/time at which the message was prepared.

Date/time at which the account servicer has set as the deadline to respond, with instructions, to an outstanding event. This time is dependent on the reference time zone of the account servicer as specified in an SLA.
Date/time at which the deal (rights) was agreed.
Date/time at which the trade was executed.

Date/time at which the account servicer has set as the deadline to respond, with instructions, to an outstanding event. This time is dependent on the reference time zone of the account servicer as specified in an SLA.
Date/time set as the deadline to respond, with instructions, to an outstanding event, for which the underlying security is out on loan.
Date/time set as the deadline to respond, with instructions, to an outstanding event, for which the underlying security is out on loan.
Number of days used for interest calculation.
Number of days used for calculating the accrued interest amount.
Number of days from the trade date that the trading party on the other side should divulge details of the transaction.
Total number of transactions taken into account in the calculation of the netting position amount.
Current allocation number.
Minimum number of days' notice a counterparty needs for terminating the transaction.

This field specifies the number of days used for calculating the accrued interest amount, that is, the number of days between interest payments starting from the date specified in field 98a qualifier LDFP.
Identifies the number of days in which the cash investor and dealer can agree to revisit the terms of an agreement.
Number of days since the last pricing update.
The number of the settlement instruction in this message in a range of linked settlement instructions.
Sequential number of the instruction in a range of linked instructions.
Sequential number of the instruction in a range of linked settlement instructions.
Total number of allocations.
Total number of collateral instructions involved in the transaction.
The total number of settlement instructions which are linked together. It is the total number of children transactions.
Total number of instructions that are linked together.
Total number of settlement instructions that are linked together.
Total number of transactions taken into account in the calculation of the netting position amount.
